                            <comment id="12577319" author="shalinmangar" created="Tue, 11 Mar 2008 07:03:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With your permission Grant, here&apos;s a patch to add this functionality.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since the facet.date response is not a homogenous NamedList of Numbers, I added the non-number members of facet date response such as GAP and END as attributes in FacetField.java The rest of the facet date responses such as date values and facet.date.other params are handling as FacetField.Count objects&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;QueryResponse has a new method getFacetDates which returns a list of FacetField (modified as above).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A simple test with a xml response for testing has been added.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12579834" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2008 13:11:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 638357.  Thanks Shalin!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12582093" author="hossman" created="Wed, 26 Mar 2008 00:48:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FYI: the QueryResponseTest added by this patch has been failing in the nightly.sh build (but not the hudson build) since it was added.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;reopening the issue until we figure out if it is a problem with teh coe added by this issue, or a larger underlying bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12582433" author="hossman" created="Wed, 26 Mar 2008 21:14:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;false alarm ... the probably was evidently an old version of ant/junit that didn&apos;t know abouthte new @Test based JUnit tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
